    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This investment-grade 13B-REW rotary powerplant features seamless sequential turbocharging and exceptional compression across all rotor faces. The chassis is a definitive example of the Type R Bathurst evolution, equipped with factory-spec Bilstein dampers and a high-rigidity strut tower brace that ensures surgical turn-in precision. Power is managed through a precise five-speed manual gearbox and delivered to the asphalt via a Torsen limited-slip differential. The exterior finish is flawless, showing no signs of oxidation or paint metamerism, while the undercarriage remains free of structural corrosion. This specimen exhibits perfect boost linearity, with the secondary Hitachi HT12 actuator engaging exactly at 4,500 RPM. A concours-level vehicle for the rotary enthusiast who demands mechanical perfection.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
